---
import SiteLayout from '@layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout title="Liri Calculator" variant="content">
  <div class="ribbon" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <article class="content-surface prose">
    <h1>Liri Calculator</h1>
    <p>
      Liri Calculator is a cross-platform, Material Design calculator,
      currently in <span class="chip">alpha</span> stage.
    </p>
    <p>
      It provides the features expected from a modern calculator while keeping
      the interface clean.
    </p>

    <h2>Features</h2>
    <div class="image-grid">
      <section>
        <h3>Straightforward</h3>
        <img src="/images/apps/calculator/screen_downloads_01.png" alt="Liri Calculator main view" />
        <p>A calculator that gets out of your way.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Solid</h3>
        <img src="/images/apps/calculator/screen_downloads_02.png" alt="Liri Calculator advanced view" />
        <p>Basic and scientific calculations are covered.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <h2>Contribute</h2>
    <p>
      Contributions can include design, code, translations, bug reports, and
      testing.
    </p>

    <h3>Design</h3>
    <p>
      Start with the
      <a href="https://github.com/lirios/calculator/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3A%22needs+design%22">GitHub issue list</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Code</h3>
    <p>
      Liri Calculator is written using Qt, C++, and QML. QtQuick Controls 2 and
      <a href="https://github.com/lirios/fluid">Fluid</a> provide the Material
      Design interface.
    </p>
    <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/lirios/calculator</code></pre>
    <md-filled-tonal-button href="https://github.com/lirios/calculator">Fork on GitHub</md-filled-tonal-button>

    <h3>Translations</h3>
    <p>Help translate Liri Calculator into your language.</p>
    <md-filled-button href="/get-involved/">Get Involved</md-filled-button>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
